snippet.textDisplay:
Oi! Tudo bem? Cheguei no seu vídeo pelo google rs
Queria tirar uma dúvida, caso já exista resposta pra ela.
Eu vacinei a primeira dose e meus pais tbm (nós 3 com a Astrazeneca), a mais de 30 dias (eu a uns 33 dias, e meus a mais ou menos uns 50 dias). Minha cunhada me chamou pra almoçar na casa dela e eu, achando que seríamos só nós, me enganei. Chamaram mais gente e no ao todo o almoço foi em 7 pessoas. Eu nunca tinha saído sozinha nesse tempo antes com tanta gente assim então imagine minha preocupação... Voltei pra casa e fiquei preocupada com ter pego o covid-19 e acabar passando ele pros meus pais. Não falei nada pra não os assustar, mas tenho lavado meu copo, lavado as mãos antes de pegar nas coisas, etc... com medo
Considerando o que falei, acha que existe possibilidade grande de eu ter pego e acabar passando?
(nesse meio tempo lá, vinha gente, me abraçava..)

texto_en:
Hi! alright? I came to your video through google lol
I wanted to ask a question, if there is already an answer for it.
I vaccinated the first dose and my parents too (in constant_numeric with astrazeneca), for more than constant_numeric days (I for a few constant_numeric days, and mine for more or less a constant_numeric days). My sister-in-law invited me to have lunch at her house and I, thinking it would be just us, was wrong. they called more people and not all the lunch was in constant_numeric people. I had never gone out alone in that time before with so many people so imagine my concern... I went back home and was worried that I had caught the constant covid_numerica and ended up passing it on to my parents. I didn't say anything so as not to scare them, but I've been washing my glass, washing my hands before picking up things, etc...
considering what I said, do you think there is a great possibility that I caught it and ended up passing?
(In the meantime there, people came, hugged me..)
